J.K. = Jiddu Krishnamurti
In his early life he was groomed to be the new World Teacher but later
rejected this mantle and withdrew from the organisation behind it. His subject
matter included psychological revolution, the nature of mind, meditation,
inquiry, human relationships, and bringing about radical change in society. He
constantly stressed the need for a revolution in the psyche of every human
being and emphasised that such revolution cannot be brought about by any
external entity, be it religious, political, or social.
